{
  "text": "Cell suspensions were lysed in a solution containing 1% Triton X-100, RNase 100 #g/ml, and propidium iodide (PI) 10 ~g/ml. Nuclei were then analyzed for DNA content by FACS \u00ae [CITATION_1] . Alternatively, cells were incubated with Hoechst 33342 dye (Sigma Chemical Co., St. Louis, MO) at a concentration of 5 ug/ml then analyzed for DNA content by FACS [CITATION_2] .",
